ity and calmness give a solid foundation, while the interpersonal issues, though important, may be managed with crew\u2011resource\u2011management training.\nGiven the weighting of safety\u2011critical factors (reliability, calmness, technical ability) over the interpersonal drawbacks, **Candidate\u202fB emerges as the strongest overall fit for the long\u2011distance pilot role**. The communication weaknesses are the primary area of risk and should be addressed in training and crew\u2011selection processes, but they do not outweigh the decisive safety\u2011related strengths.\n**Open question for the group:**\nDoes anyone have any additional information on **Candidate\u202fA\u2019s teamwork or communication abilities** (beyond being \u201cunfriendly\u201d) or on **Candidate\u202fD\u2019s leadership style** (beyond \u201crelatively weak leadership\u201d and being \u201carrogant\u201d)? Any further details could help confirm or adjust the current assessment.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We have gathered additional info from agents 1 and 2 about D teamwork and B teamwork, plus technical strengths for A, C, D. Now we need to produce our public contribution: summarize assessment, incorporate new info, possibly ask further clarifying questions if needed, and give vote.\n\nWe have now full set of attributes:\n\nLet's compile all known attributes per candidate:\n\nCandidate A:\n- Anticipates dangerous situations.\n- Able to see complex connections.\n- Excellent spatial vision.\n- Very good leadership qualities.\n- Unfriendly.\n- Eats unhealthily.\n- (From earlier maybe also \"not open to new ideas\"? Actually original list: \"Candidate A can anticipate dangerous situations. Candidate A is able to see complex connections. Candidate A has excellent spatial vision. Candidate A has very good leadership qualities. Candidate A is unfriendly. Candidate A eats unhealthily.\" No mention of not open to new ideas. That was from ear